rComments: i really did not like this prof or the class. he would yell at his student and was rude. do not take any of his classes.
Hilarious teacher, knows his stuff and highly engaging. Don't miss a class and make sure to pay attention and complete the work given! Great content.

Gustavo is pretty caring and funny, i found that he could be a bit curt sometimes but that was usually when a stupid question was asked of him, so fair enough. Really funny guy, also really likes participation. His tests arent hard, but youre screwed if you dont study and just rely on ctrl+f

I hated this class. I was in my first year when I took this class and the prof really put me off university. I thought uni was about being treated like an adult but this prof was rude, spoke down to his students and was angry all the time. He would make me cry all the time and was very harsh! I WOULD HIGHLY RECOMMEND TO NOT TAKE A CLASS WITH HIM!!

Since going online he has become one of the worst profs I have ever had. He is a very rude person, if u have any questions dont even bother asking them because he will make you feel so stupid. He is very passive aggressive. His slides look like theyve been done by a 5th grader, filled with spelling errors and not helpful. Would never recommend.

Since online learning has been the go-to, he's totally changed. I used to love him as a prof, not anymore. He became extremely passive-aggressive and did not seem to enjoy teaching anymore. I feel like he has trouble separating himself as a person and himself as a prof. Huge micro-manager.

I love Gustavo, if you literally just talk/interact with him you'll understand his humour type. He makes an effort to know each and every one of his students. The classes can we weird because Linguistics isn't like any other subject, but once you get the hang of it, its awesome. His exams are so much fun, I got a 100% on my final in this class.

Prof Freire is very passionate about linguistics and loves when students participate in class discussions. Despite the other reviews, I wouldn't consider him harsh, he's actually very caring and wants his students to succeed and is always available outside of class. I'd definitely recommend him as a prof!
My experience was very different from the others. He was nice and gave me as many chances as I could. We would often meet and discuss the content and assignments. I learned quite a lot

He's a very knowledgeable man, but very cruel. Even when I got good grades he was extremely harsh in his written critiques. I've honestly cried reading his feedback, it's quite cruel. He's very specific but vague in his rubrics. I liked the content but he was unnecessarily harsh.

This professor definitely made class more cruel than it needed to be. The class averages were always really low, and he would get mad at us for doing poorly. Up to a certain point, I feel like teachers should change a little too if everyone is doing bad all the time, which never happened. I do not recommend.

Probably a good prof in person but online was brutal. Assignment instructions are unclear, feedback is harsh, pretty short lectures, and prepare to feel dumb if you don't understand something. Students discretion is advised :/

Absolutely hate how this prof approached online school. He was very passive-aggressive, I found, and he got mad at students for not doing well. He speeds through his lectures so write quickly! Oh, he also made a "joke" about people dying during the pandemic. Very unprofessional.
Gustavo is the best dude Im obsessed with him. His French is questionable but like same lol. Take his class fr hes so sweet. You better write fast tho cause this kid SPEEDS through his slides lmao

Took us out for drinks after the semester, was very funny and very knowledgable. I loved his class and teaching style. He cares about students a lot, very personable but I do agree with some of the others, he can be over the top sometimes. He sometimes makes jokes at other people's expense but it's in good fun.

I can't stand this prof. Completely disrespectful and rude. He doesn't give clear instructions for the assignments but will get mad at his students for not doing well?? His teaching is also confusing because he'll jump from slide to slide, making it extremely hard to follow. I wouldn't recommend his class.

He is knowledgeable , but a horrible teacher. Very unclear grading criteria, he seems to enjoy mocking students who are confused; I always left the class feeling discouraged. Sidenote: He often uses slurs or innappropriate language in class. I am not one of those hyper-PC easily-offended people, but it's unprofessional.
He is very funny and passionate. If you go to his office hours, he will know you are dedicated to his class and he will give you back the favour. There is a lot of work but it was really fun

Great Prof! Take him for intro Linguistics courses. He does go through the information very quickly, though if you stay on top of everything you will do well. He also really wants his students to thrive, always giving extra help. One thing that really stood out about Gustavo, he learns almost every student's name.
Very good professor and very active, seems enthusiastic about what he teaches.

Honestly a great class. The professor is very passionate about the subject, and it shows in his teaching. Beware of the 10 person group project. It'll be a struggle, but it will be worth it in the end. Midterm and homework are easy if you read the papers and pay attention. Be creative in your projects and essays!
nice

BRAZILIAN. FUNNY. AWESOME. He's so funny and cool, rocks the manbun, loves to make jokes and insert jokes in his pwr-points as well lol Every requirements for the tests/quizzes are posted in advance and are clear, but you rly gotta read the textbook, study the slides and listen in class to have a good grade Very helpful and kind, TAs were great too

Freire is by far the best prof I've ever had at uOttawa. If you attend all lectures, DGDs, do all your homework assignments, then you should do well. I found that the material can be confusing in class but clarifying concepts with Freire outside of class really helped. He's extremely friendly, approachable, and his jokes in class will kill you.

Outstanding professor! He made every class not only bearable, but fun and interesting! The course is content heavy, but the workload is very manageable. Gustavo puts a lot of effort into making sure you understand everything. I was amazed at how much he cares about the success of his students. I would 100% recommend this prof :)
Amazing prof who honestly cares about his students success. Content is heavy, but he teaches it in an interesting way. He is really fun and passionate!

I've never before had a prof who cares so much about my success in their class. Was always available to talk outside of class and knows each student by name. Material on tests was very fair and his lectures were fun and engaging. Hoping I can take another one of his courses next semester!

Gustavo is a wonderful professor and I've enjoyed all my classes with him. He's very adamant on the success of his students and keep classes very casual (conversational) and encourages student participation. Some students may dislike this teaching style, however I have found this method to improve my ability to think critically.

Im very happy I took this class! He conveys the course content in a fun way and he is very funny. Has clear expectations and truly cares for his students. Would not hesitate to take another class with him!

Loved the course content, actually made linguistics interesting. Prof was awesome. Clarification/expectations for on what could be on the tests could be a bit more clear. TA and prof should have more communication for what to expect with marking.

The course was very informative and very useful for most of the linguistics students who are considering grad school in Speech Path. The teaching was stimulating (as he walked around often which kept you awake). Gustavo is an excellent professor, he uses different methods to accommodate different learners (videos, articles, etc)

J'ai adoré le style d'enseignement. C'était dynamique et stimulant. Les devoirs reflètent bien la matière, et aident à assurer la compréhension.L'examen reflétait aussi la matière. J'ai aimé que le prof a mis l'effort de apprendre tous nos noms. Merci! :)
Gustavo est très sympathique et positif et il encourage beaucoup la discussion de groupe; ce que j'apprécie beaucoup. Bonnes exemples en classe.
Tellement un bon prof. Dynamique et joyeuxTrès stimulant en classe et répond très rapidement aux courriels des étudiants. Les examens reflètent bien le contenu du cours.

La matière était intéressante et le prof a fait plusieurs retours pour s'assurer que tout le monde comprend. Beaucoup d'exemples, PowerPoints disponibles en ligne, examen représentatif du contenu. Gustavo est dynamique et joyeux et il vise vraiment le succès pour ses étudiants (meilleur intérêt). Toujours disponible pour des questions.
Funny but not a great teacher
He knows his stuff and knows how to explain it. Classes are chill and fun. Easy to follow and he encourages questions and debates. I would certainly take anothe class with him
Funny, caring and ALWAYS available when I needed help. Very approachable as well. He is passionate about what he teaches! Loved his course.
By far one of the best profs I've had, he cares about his students, goes out of his way to learn their names. He is always available for office hours or whenever needed. Definitely recommend.

A very funny, caring professor very available to students outside of class. He marks very fairly and not based off of a strict answer key. Really appreciates creativity and energy, so keep that in mind for assignments as well as presentations.
Had Gustavo last semester again. I love his classes and the energy he puts to motivate and encourage students. Very caring and funny. Was always available to help students.

I'm learning a lot this semester with him. He is very funny and approachable, knows students by their names and wants you to do well. I would certainly take his class again and I would certainly recommend him to anyone. One of the best professors I have ever had!

He is a very cool prof. Caring and attentive, I do not agree with the others. He is very helpful and did not belittle me even when my questions were stupid. I would definitely take other classes with him. His language can be off sometimes, but that's what makes it fun

One of my favorite professors in the linguistics department. Doesn't expect you to memorize dates or random information. Quizzes and exams are based on deep overall knowledge of the main ideas. Remembers students by name and is engaging and helpful. Purposefully switched into his class again this semester!

Even though I did really well in this class my experience with this professor is awful. He has absolutely no patience for your struggle. Though he is approachable after class he is more likely to belittle you for not knowing something than to actually help. Also, he rambles during lectures and never finishes on time.
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Group projects', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: While he is funny, there is a fair amount of readings.

Did not like this prof at all. Had a tendency to use slurs in class. Was very ad lib about his lectures and homework assignments, frequently not giving clear information about homework up until the due date, sometimes not even then. Will give him credit, frequently does not require a textbook and the material was easy

A very funny, caring professor who's easy to pay attention to during lectures and is very available to students outside of class. His expectations are a little unclear, but he marks very fairly and not based off of a strict answer key. Really appreciates creativity and energy, so keep that in mind for assignments as well as presentations.
Had Gustavo last semester, really great professor, and very invested in all of his students. Hopefully I can take another class with him!
